 <sect1 id="release-8-2-23">
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Release 8.2.23</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>版本 8.2.23</title>

  <formalpara>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<title>Release date:</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<title>发布日期：</title>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <para>2011-12-05</para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <para>2011-12-05</para>
  </formalpara>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   This release contains a variety of fixes from 8.2.22.
   For information about new features in the 8.2 major release, see
   <xref linkend="release-8-2">.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个版本包含各种自8.2.22以来的修复。关于8.2主版本的新特性信息，
请查看<xref linkend="release-8-2">。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   This is expected to be the last <productname>PostgreSQL</> release
   in the 8.2.X series.  Users are encouraged to update to a newer
   release branch soon.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这预计是8.2.X系列的最后一个<productname>PostgreSQL</>版本。
建议用户尽快更新到一个新的版本分支。
</para>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Migration to Version 8.2.23</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>迁移到版本 8.2.23</title>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
    A dump/restore is not required for those running 8.2.X.
   </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
运行8.2.X的用户不需要转储/恢复。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
    However, a longstanding error was discovered in the definition of the
    <literal>information_schema.referential_constraints</> view.  If you
    rely on correct results from that view, you should replace its
    definition as explained in the first changelog item below.
   </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
不过，在<literal>information_schema.referential_constraints</>
视图的定义中发现一个长期存在的错误。如果你依赖于该视图的正确结果，
你应该像下面解释的第一个更新日志项一样替换它的定义。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
    Also, if you are upgrading from a version earlier than 8.2.14,
    see <xref linkend="release-8-2-14">.
   </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
还有，如果你是从一个早于8.2.14的版本升级而来，那么请查看<xref linkend="release-8-2-14">。
</para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Changes</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>修改列表</title>

   <itemizedlist>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix bugs in <literal>information_schema.referential_constraints</> view
      (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复在<literal>information_schema.referential_constraints</>视图中的错误 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This view was being insufficiently careful about matching the
      foreign-key constraint to the depended-on primary or unique key
      constraint.  That could result in failure to show a foreign key
      constraint at all, or showing it multiple times, or claiming that it
      depends on a different constraint than the one it really does.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个视图在匹配外键约束到决定性的主键或唯一键约束上不够细心。
这会导致未能显示外键约束，或者多次显示外键约束，
或者抱怨它依赖于一个与它实际依赖的不同的约束。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Since the view definition is installed by <application>initdb</>,
      merely upgrading will not fix the problem.  If you need to fix this
      in an existing installation, you can (as a superuser) drop the
      <literal>information_schema</> schema then re-create it by sourcing
      <filename><replaceable>SHAREDIR</>/information_schema.sql</filename>.
      (Run <literal>pg_config -&minus;sharedir</> if you're uncertain where
      <replaceable>SHAREDIR</> is.)  This must be repeated in each database
      to be fixed.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
因为视图定义是通过<application>initdb</>安装的，只是升级将不能修复该问题。
如果你需要在一个现有的安装中修复该问题，你可以（作为超级用户）
删除<literal>information_schema</>模式，然后通过来源
<filename><replaceable>SHAREDIR</>/information_schema.sql</filename>
重新创建它。（如果不确定<replaceable>SHAREDIR</>在哪里，运行
<literal>pg_config --sharedir</>。）必须在每个要修复的数据库中重复该步骤。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix TOAST-related data corruption during <literal>CREATE TABLE dest AS
      SELECT * FROM src</> or <literal>INSERT INTO dest SELECT * FROM src</>
      (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复<literal>CREATE TABLE dest AS SELECT * FROM src</>或
<literal>INSERT INTO dest SELECT * FROM src</>期间TOAST相关的数据损坏 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      If a table has been modified by <command>ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN</>,
      attempts to copy its data verbatim to another table could produce
      corrupt results in certain corner cases.
      The problem can only manifest in this precise form in 8.4 and later,
      but we patched earlier versions as well in case there are other code
      paths that could trigger the same bug.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
如果一个表通过<command>ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN</>修改了，
那么尝试逐字的拷贝它的数据到另外一个表可能在极端情况下产生损坏的结果。
这个问题只能在8.4及以后的版本中以这个精确的形式来验证，
不过我们也给早期的版本打了补丁，以防有其他的代码路径会触发相同的错误。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix race condition during toast table access from stale syscache entries
      (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复toast表访问陈旧的系统缓存记录时的竞态条件 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      The typical symptom was transient errors like <quote>missing chunk
      number 0 for toast value NNNNN in pg_toast_2619</>, where the cited
      toast table would always belong to a system catalog.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
典型的症状是像<quote>missing chunk number 0 for toast value NNNNN in pg_toast_2619</>
这样的瞬态错误，这里引用的toast表将总是属于一个系统目录。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Improve locale support in <type>money</> type's input and output
      (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
改善<type>money</>类型的输入和输出中的本地支持 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Aside from not supporting all standard
      <link linkend="guc-lc-monetary"><varname>lc_monetary</></link>
      formatting options, the input and output functions were inconsistent,
      meaning there were locales in which dumped <type>money</> values could
      not be re-read.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
除了不支持所有标准的<link linkend="guc-lc-monetary"><varname>lc_monetary</></link>
格式选项之外，输入和输出函数是不考虑的，意味着有的环境中转储的<type>money</>
值不能被重新读取。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Don't let <link
      linkend="guc-transform-null-equals"><varname>transform_null_equals</></link>
      affect <literal>CASE foo WHEN NULL ...</> constructs
      (Heikki Linnakangas)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
让<link linkend="guc-transform-null-equals"><varname>transform_null_equals</></link>
不影响<literal>CASE foo WHEN NULL ...</>结构 (Heikki Linnakangas)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      <varname>transform_null_equals</> is only supposed to affect
      <literal>foo = NULL</> expressions written directly by the user, not
      equality checks generated internally by this form of <literal>CASE</>.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
<varname>transform_null_equals</>只应该影响直接由用户编写的<literal>foo = NULL</>
表达式，不等于<literal>CASE</>的这个格式内部产生的检查。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Change foreign-key trigger creation order to better support
      self-referential foreign keys (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修改外键触发器创建，要求更好的支持自我引用的外键 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      For a cascading foreign key that references its own table, a row update
      will fire both the <literal>ON UPDATE</> trigger and the
      <literal>CHECK</> trigger as one event.  The <literal>ON UPDATE</>
      trigger must execute first, else the <literal>CHECK</> will check a
      non-final state of the row and possibly throw an inappropriate error.
      However, the firing order of these triggers is determined by their
      names, which generally sort in creation order since the triggers have
      auto-generated names following the convention
      <quote>RI_ConstraintTrigger_NNNN</>.  A proper fix would require
      modifying that convention, which we will do in 9.2, but it seems risky
      to change it in existing releases.  So this patch just changes the
      creation order of the triggers.  Users encountering this type of error
      should drop and re-create the foreign key constraint to get its
      triggers into the right order.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
对于一个引用自身的表的级联外键，一个行更新将作为一个事件触发<literal>ON UPDATE</>
触发器和<literal>CHECK</>触发器。必须先执行<literal>ON UPDATE</>触发器，
否则<literal>CHECK</>将检查一个行的非最终状态，并且可能抛出一个不合适的错误。
然而，这些触发器的触发顺序是通过他们的名字决定的，通常以特定的顺序排序，
因为触发器有自动生成的名字，遵从约定<quote>RI_ConstraintTrigger_NNNN</>。
修改该约定将需要一个适当的修复，我们将在9.2中实现，
但是在现有的版本中修改它似乎是危险的。所以这个路径只是改变了触发器的创建顺序。
用户遇到这个类型的错误时应该删除并重建外键约束，以使它的触发器的顺序正确。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Preserve blank lines within commands in <application>psql</>'s command
      history (Robert Haas)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
保护<application>psql</>命令历史中的命令中的空行 (Robert Haas)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      The former behavior could cause problems if an empty line was removed
      from within a string literal, for example.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
例如，如果从一个字符串文本中删除了一个空行，前者的行为会导致问题。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Use the preferred version of <application>xsubpp</> to build PL/Perl,
      not necessarily the operating system's main copy
      (David Wheeler and Alex Hunsaker)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
使用<application>xsubpp</>的首选版本建立PL/Perl，
不一定是操作系统的主要拷贝 (David Wheeler 和 Alex Hunsaker)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Honor query cancel interrupts promptly in <function>pgstatindex()</>
      (Robert Haas)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
遵从<function>pgstatindex()</>中的查询取消立即中断 (Robert Haas)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Ensure VPATH builds properly install all server header files
      (Peter Eisentraut)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
确保VPATH构建适当的安装所有的服务器头文件 (Peter Eisentraut)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Shorten file names reported in verbose error messages (Peter Eisentraut)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
缩短在详细错误消息中报告的文件名 (Peter Eisentraut)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Regular builds have always reported just the name of the C file
      containing the error message call, but VPATH builds formerly
      reported an absolute path name.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
常规的构建总是只是报告包含错误消息调用的C文件的名字，
但是VPATH构建以前报告一个绝对路径名。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix interpretation of Windows timezone names for Central America
      (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
为Central America修复Windows时区名的解释 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Map <quote>Central America Standard Time</> to <literal>CST6</>, not
      <literal>CST6CDT</>, because DST is generally not observed anywhere in
      Central America.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
映射<quote>Central America Standard Time</>到<literal>CST6</>，
而不是<literal>CST6CDT</>，因为DST通常没有观察到Central America的每一个地方。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Update time zone data files to <application>tzdata</> release 2011n
      for DST law changes in Brazil, Cuba, Fiji, Palestine, Russia, and Samoa;
      also historical corrections for Alaska and British East Africa.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
更新时区数据文件到<application>tzdata</>版本2011n，因为DST规律在
Brazil、Cuba、Fiji、Palestine、Russia和Samoa发生了改变；
还为Alaska和British East Africa做了历史纠正。
</para>
    </listitem>

   </itemizedlist>

  </sect2>
 </sect1>

 <sect1 id="release-8-2-22">
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Release 8.2.22</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>版本 8.2.22</title>

  <formalpara>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<title>Release date:</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<title>发布日期：</title>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <para>2011-09-26</para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <para>2011-09-26</para>
  </formalpara>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   This release contains a variety of fixes from 8.2.21.
   For information about new features in the 8.2 major release, see
   <xref linkend="release-8-2">.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个版本包含各种自8.2.21以来的修复。关于8.2主版本的新特性信息，
请查看<xref linkend="release-8-2">。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   The <productname>PostgreSQL</> community will stop releasing updates
   for the 8.2.X release series in December 2011.
   Users are encouraged to update to a newer release branch soon.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
<productname>PostgreSQL</>社区将在2011年12月停止对8.2.X版本系列发布更新。
建议用户尽快更新到一个新的版本分支。
</para>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Migration to Version 8.2.22</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>迁移到版本 8.2.22</title>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
    A dump/restore is not required for those running 8.2.X.
    However, if you are upgrading from a version earlier than 8.2.14,
    see <xref linkend="release-8-2-14">.
   </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
运行8.2.X的用户不需要转储/恢复。不过，如果你是从一个早于8.2.14的版本升级而来，
那么请查看<xref linkend="release-8-2-14">。
</para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Changes</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>修改列表</title>

   <itemizedlist>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix multiple bugs in GiST index page split processing (Heikki
      Linnakangas)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复GiST索引页分裂处理中的多个错误 (Heikki Linnakangas)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      The probability of occurrence was low, but these could lead to index
      corruption.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
发生的可能性很低，但是会导致索引损坏。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Avoid possibly accessing off the end of memory in <command>ANALYZE</>
      (Noah Misch)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
避免<command>ANALYZE</>中可能的访问关闭内存的结尾 (Noah Misch)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This fixes a very-low-probability server crash scenario.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这修复了一个非常低可能的服务器崩溃情况。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix race condition in relcache init file invalidation (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复relcache初始化文件失效中的竞态条件 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      There was a window wherein a new backend process could read a stale init
      file but miss the inval messages that would tell it the data is stale.
      The result would be bizarre failures in catalog accesses, typically
      <quote>could not read block 0 in file ...</> later during startup.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
新的后端进程中有一个窗口会读取陈旧的初始化文件，
但是错过会告诉它该数据是陈旧的的inval消息。
结果会是目录访问中奇怪的失败，典型的是在启动后
<quote>could not read block 0 in file ...</>。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix memory leak at end of a GiST index scan (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复GiST索引扫描结束时的内存泄露 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Commands that perform many separate GiST index scans, such as
      verification of a new GiST-based exclusion constraint on a table
      already containing many rows, could transiently require large amounts of
      memory due to this leak.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
执行许多独立GiST索引扫描的命令，比如在一个早已包含许多行的表上新建基于GiST的排除约束的验证，
由于这个泄露，可能会在瞬间需要大量的内存。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix performance problem when constructing a large, lossy bitmap
      (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复构建一个大型的、有损耗的位图时的性能问题 (Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix array- and path-creating functions to ensure padding bytes are
      zeroes (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复数组和路径创建函数，确保填充字节是零 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This avoids some situations where the planner will think that
      semantically-equal constants are not equal, resulting in poor
      optimization.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这避免了一些规划器认为语义上相等的常数不等，导致欠佳的最优化的情况。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Work around gcc 4.6.0 bug that breaks WAL replay (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
绕开中断WAL重放的gcc 4.6.0 bug (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This could lead to loss of committed transactions after a server crash.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这可能导致在服务器崩溃后丢失已提交的事务。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix dump bug for <literal>VALUES</> in a view (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复一个视图中<literal>VALUES</>的转储bug (Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Disallow <literal>SELECT FOR UPDATE/SHARE</> on sequences (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
不允许在一个序列上<literal>SELECT FOR UPDATE/SHARE</> (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This operation doesn't work as expected and can lead to failures.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个操作不想预期的那样工作，并且会导致失败。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Defend against integer overflow when computing size of a hash table (Tom
      Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
计算一个哈希表的大小时，防止整数溢出 (Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix portability bugs in use of credentials control messages for
      <quote>peer</> authentication (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复<quote>peer</>认证的证书控制消息中正在使用的潜在的bug (Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix typo in <function>pg_srand48</> seed initialization (Andres Freund)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复<function>pg_srand48</>种子的初始化中的打印错误 (Andres Freund)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This led to failure to use all bits of the provided seed.  This function
      is not used on most platforms (only those without <function>srandom</>),
      and the potential security exposure from a less-random-than-expected
      seed seems minimal in any case.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这导致未能使用提供的种子的所有位。这个函数没有在大多数平台上使用
（只有那些没有<function>srandom</>的平台），并且在任何情况下，
比预期的随机少的多下种子似乎很小，有潜在的安全风险。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
