  <title>版本 8.2.20</title>

  <formalpara>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<title>Release date:</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<title>发布日期：</title>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <para>2011-01-31</para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <para>2011-01-31</para>
  </formalpara>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   This release contains a variety of fixes from 8.2.19.
   For information about new features in the 8.2 major release, see
   <xref linkend="release-8-2">.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个版本包含各种自8.2.19以来的修复。关于8.2主版本的新特性信息，
请查看<xref linkend="release-8-2">。
</para>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Migration to Version 8.2.20</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>迁移到版本 8.2.20</title>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
    A dump/restore is not required for those running 8.2.X.
    However, if you are upgrading from a version earlier than 8.2.14,
    see <xref linkend="release-8-2-14">.
   </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
运行8.2.X的用户不需要转储/恢复。不过，如果你是从一个早于8.2.14的版本升级而来，
那么请查看<xref linkend="release-8-2-14">。
</para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Changes</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>修改列表</title>

   <itemizedlist>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Avoid failures when <command>EXPLAIN</> tries to display a simple-form
      <literal>CASE</> expression (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
避免<command>EXPLAIN</>尝试显示一个<literal>CASE</>表达式的简单格式时的失败 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      If the <literal>CASE</>'s test expression was a constant, the planner
      could simplify the <literal>CASE</> into a form that confused the
      expression-display code, resulting in <quote>unexpected CASE WHEN
      clause</> errors.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
如果<literal>CASE</>的测试表达式是一个常量，规划器将简化<literal>CASE</>
为一个混淆表达式显示代码的格式，导致<quote>unexpected CASE WHEN clause</>错误。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix assignment to an array slice that is before the existing range
      of subscripts (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复分配给数组切片的下标在现有范围之前 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      If there was a gap between the newly added subscripts and the first
      pre-existing subscript, the code miscalculated how many entries needed
      to be copied from the old array's null bitmap, potentially leading to
      data corruption or crash.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
如果在新添加的下标和已经存在的下标之间存在间隔，
代码错误计算有多少项需要从老的数组的空位图中拷贝，
潜在的导致数据损坏或崩溃。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Avoid unexpected conversion overflow in planner for very distant date
      values (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
避免规划器中非常遥远的日期值意外的转换溢出 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      The <type>date</> type supports a wider range of dates than can be
      represented by the <type>timestamp</> types, but the planner assumed it
      could always convert a date to timestamp with impunity.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
<type>date</>类型比<type>timestamp</>类型可以表示的日期支持的范围更加广泛，
但是规划器假设它总是可以将日期转换为时间戳而不受惩罚。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix <application>pg_restore</>'s text output for large objects (BLOBs)
      when <varname>standard_conforming_strings</> is on (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复启用<varname>standard_conforming_strings</>时，
<application>pg_restore</>为大对象(BLOBs)的文本输出 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Although restoring directly to a database worked correctly, string
      escaping was incorrect if <application>pg_restore</> was asked for
      SQL text output and <varname>standard_conforming_strings</> had been
      enabled in the source database.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
尽管直接恢复到一个数据库能正确的工作，但是如果<application>pg_restore</>
要求SQL文本输出和<varname>standard_conforming_strings</>已经在源数据库中启用了的话，
字符串的转义是不正确的。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix erroneous parsing of <type>tsquery</> values containing
      <literal>... &amp; !(subexpression) | ...</literal> (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复包含<literal>... &amp; !(subexpression) | ...</literal>
的<type>tsquery</>值的错误解析 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Queries containing this combination of operators were not executed
      correctly.  The same error existed in <filename>contrib/intarray</>'s
      <type>query_int</> type and <filename>contrib/ltree</>'s
      <type>ltxtquery</> type.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
包含这种操作符组合的查询没有正确的执行，相同的错误存在于<filename>contrib/intarray</>
的<type>query_int</>类型和<filename>contrib/ltree</>的<type>ltxtquery</>类型中。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix buffer overrun in <filename>contrib/intarray</>'s input function
      for the <type>query_int</> type (Apple)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
为<type>query_int</>类型修复<filename>contrib/intarray</>的输入函数中的缓冲区溢出 (Apple)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This bug is a security risk since the function's return address could
      be overwritten.  Thanks to Apple Inc's security team for reporting this
      issue and supplying the fix.  (CVE-2010-4015)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个错误是一个安全风险，因为该函数的返回地址可能会被重写。
感谢Apple Inc的安全团队报告这个问题并且提供该修复。 (CVE-2010-4015)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix bug in <filename>contrib/seg</>'s GiST picksplit algorithm
      (Alexander Korotkov)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复<filename>contrib/seg</>的GiST picksplit算法中的bug (Alexander Korotkov)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This could result in considerable inefficiency, though not actually
      incorrect answers, in a GiST index on a <type>seg</> column.
      If you have such an index, consider <command>REINDEX</>ing it after
      installing this update.  (This is identical to the bug that was fixed in
      <filename>contrib/cube</> in the previous update.)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这会导致相当大的低效，尽管不是真的错误回复，在<type>seg</>字段的GiST索引中。
如果你有这样的一个索引，考虑在安装这个更新之后<command>REINDEX</>它。
（这和在以前的更新中的<filename>contrib/cube</>中修复的错误相同。）
</para>
    </listitem>

   </itemizedlist>

  </sect2>
 </sect1>

