 </sect1>

 <sect1 id="release-8-2-18">
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Release 8.2.18</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>版本 8.2.18</title>

  <formalpara>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<title>Release date:</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<title>发布日期：</title>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <para>2010-10-04</para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <para>2010-10-04</para>
  </formalpara>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   This release contains a variety of fixes from 8.2.17.
   For information about new features in the 8.2 major release, see
   <xref linkend="release-8-2">.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个版本包含各种自8.2.17以来的修复。关于8.2主版本的新特性信息，
请查看<xref linkend="release-8-2">。
</para>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Migration to Version 8.2.18</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>迁移到版本 8.2.18</title>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
    A dump/restore is not required for those running 8.2.X.
    However, if you are upgrading from a version earlier than 8.2.14,
    see <xref linkend="release-8-2-14">.
   </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
运行8.2.X的用户不需要转储/恢复。不过，如果你是从一个早于8.2.14的版本升级而来，
那么请查看<xref linkend="release-8-2-14">。
</para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Changes</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>修改列表</title>

   <itemizedlist>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Use a separate interpreter for each calling SQL userid in PL/Perl and
      PL/Tcl (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
为每个在PL/Perl和PL/Tcl中调用的SQL userid使用一个单独的解释器 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This change prevents security problems that can be caused by subverting
      Perl or Tcl code that will be executed later in the same session under
      another SQL user identity (for example, within a <literal>SECURITY
      DEFINER</> function).  Most scripting languages offer numerous ways that
      that might be done, such as redefining standard functions or operators
      called by the target function.  Without this change, any SQL user with
      Perl or Tcl language usage rights can do essentially anything with the
      SQL privileges of the target function's owner.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个修改阻止了通过破坏稍后由另一个SQL用户身份在同一个会话中执行的Perl或Tcl
代码引起的安全问题（例如，在一个<literal>SECURITY DEFINER</>函数中）。
大多数脚本语言提供多种可能实现的方式，比如重新定义被目标函数调用的标准函数或操作符。
没有这个修改，任何拥有Perl或Tcl语言使用权限的SQL用户基本上都可以用目标函数所有者的SQL
权限做任何事情。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      The cost of this change is that intentional communication among Perl
      and Tcl functions becomes more difficult.  To provide an escape hatch,
      PL/PerlU and PL/TclU functions continue to use only one interpreter
      per session.  This is not considered a security issue since all such
      functions execute at the trust level of a database superuser already.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个修改的代价是Perl和Tcl函数之间有意的沟通变得更加困难。
为了提供一个安全出口，PL/PerlU和PL/TclU函数继续每个会话只使用一个解释器。
这不认为是一个安全问题，因为所有这样的函数都早已在数据库超级用户的信任级别执行。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      It is likely that third-party procedural languages that claim to offer
      trusted execution have similar security issues.  We advise contacting
      the authors of any PL you are depending on for security-critical
      purposes.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
有可能第三方过程语言提供的受信任的执行有相似的安全问题。
我们建议为了安全鉴定的目的，联系任何你依赖的PL的作者。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Our thanks to Tim Bunce for pointing out this issue (CVE-2010-3433).
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
感谢Tim Bunce指出这个问题 (CVE-2010-3433)。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Prevent possible crashes in <function>pg_get_expr()</> by disallowing
      it from being called with an argument that is not one of the system
      catalog columns it's intended to be used with
      (Heikki Linnakangas, Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
通过不允许<function>pg_get_expr()</>被一个不是系统目录字段的参数调用，
阻止它中可能的崩溃 (Heikki Linnakangas, Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix Windows shared-memory allocation code
      (Tsutomu Yamada, Magnus Hagander)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复Windows共享内存分配代码 (Tsutomu Yamada, Magnus Hagander)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This bug led to the often-reported <quote>could not reattach to shared
      memory</quote> error message.  This is a back-patch of a fix that was
      applied to newer branches some time ago.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个错误导致经常报道<quote>不能重新连接上共享内存</quote>错误消息。
这是一个后向修复，前段时间已经应用到了新的分支。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Treat exit code 128 (<literal>ERROR_WAIT_NO_CHILDREN</>) as non-fatal on
      Windows (Magnus Hagander)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
在Windows上将退出代码128(<literal>ERROR_WAIT_NO_CHILDREN</>)看做非严重错误 (Magnus Hagander)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Under high load, Windows processes will sometimes fail at startup with
      this error code.  Formerly the postmaster treated this as a panic
      condition and restarted the whole database, but that seems to be
      an overreaction.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
在高负载下，Windows进程有时会带有这个错误代码在启动时失败。
以前主进程将它看做一个恐慌条件，并重启整个数据库，但是这样看起来像是过度反应。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix possible duplicate scans of <literal>UNION ALL</> member relations
      (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复可能的<literal>UNION ALL</>成员关系的重复扫描 (Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix <quote>cannot handle unplanned sub-select</quote> error (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复<quote>不能处理未计划的子查询</quote>错误 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This occurred when a sub-select contains a join alias reference that
      expands into an expression containing another sub-select.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这在子查询包含一个扩展成包含另一个子查询的表达式的连接别名引用时发生。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Reduce PANIC to ERROR in some occasionally-reported btree failure cases,
      and provide additional detail in the resulting error messages
      (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
降低某些偶然报告的btree失败情况中的PANIC为ERROR，
并在结果错误消息中提供额外的详细信息 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This should improve the system's robustness with corrupted indexes.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这会提高系统损坏索引的鲁棒性。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Prevent show_session_authorization() from crashing within autovacuum
      processes (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
阻止show_session_authorization()在自动清理进程中崩溃 (Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Defend against functions returning setof record where not all the
      returned rows are actually of the same rowtype (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
防御函数返回的记录集中不是所有返回的行都是相同的行类型 (Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix possible failure when hashing a pass-by-reference function result
      (Tao Ma, Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复哈希一个通过引用传递的函数结果时可能的失败 (Tao Ma, Tom Lane)
