  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Migration to Version 8.2.15</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>迁移到版本 8.2.15</title>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
    A dump/restore is not required for those running 8.2.X.
    However, if you are upgrading from a version earlier than 8.2.14,
    see <xref linkend="release-8-2-14">.
   </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
运行8.2.X的用户不需要转储/恢复。不过，如果你是从一个早于8.2.14的版本升级而来，
那么请查看<xref linkend="release-8-2-14">。
</para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Changes</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>修改列表</title>

   <itemizedlist>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Protect against indirect security threats caused by index functions
      changing session-local state (Gurjeet Singh, Tom)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
防御由于索引函数改变会话本地状态引起的间接安全威胁 (Gurjeet Singh, Tom)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This change prevents allegedly-immutable index functions from possibly
      subverting a superuser's session (CVE-2009-4136).
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个修改阻止了据说不变的索引函数有可能破坏超级用户的会话 (CVE-2009-4136)。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Reject SSL certificates containing an embedded null byte in the common
      name (CN) field (Magnus)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
拒绝在公共名（CN）字段中包含一个嵌入的空字节的SSL认证 (Magnus)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This prevents unintended matching of a certificate to a server or client
      name during SSL validation (CVE-2009-4034).
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这阻止了SSL校验期间证书到服务器或客户端名的无意的匹配 (CVE-2009-4034)。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix possible crash during backend-startup-time cache initialization (Tom)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复后端启动时缓存初始化期间可能的崩溃 (Tom)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Prevent signals from interrupting <literal>VACUUM</> at unsafe times
      (Alvaro)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
阻止信号在不安全的时间中断<literal>VACUUM</> (Alvaro)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This fix prevents a PANIC if a <literal>VACUUM FULL</> is canceled
      after it's already committed its tuple movements, as well as transient
      errors if a plain <literal>VACUUM</> is interrupted after having
      truncated the table.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个修复阻止了<literal>VACUUM FULL</>在它早已提交了它的元组活动之后取消时的PANIC，
和规划<literal>VACUUM</>在截断表之后被打断时的瞬态错误。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix possible crash due to integer overflow in hash table size
      calculation (Tom)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复由于哈希表大小计算中整数溢出引起的可能的崩溃 (Tom)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This could occur with extremely large planner estimates for the size of
      a hashjoin's result.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这在哈希连接的结果的大小有非常大的规划器估计时可能发生。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix very rare crash in <type>inet</>/<type>cidr</> comparisons (Chris
      Mikkelson)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复<type>inet</>/<type>cidr</>比较中非常少见的崩溃 (Chris Mikkelson)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Ensure that shared tuple-level locks held by prepared transactions are
      not ignored (Heikki)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
确保没有忽略被预备事务持有的共享元组级别锁 (Heikki)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix premature drop of temporary files used for a cursor that is accessed
      within a subtransaction (Heikki)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复用于在一个子事务中存取的游标的临时文件的过早删除 (Heikki)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix incorrect logic for GiST index page splits, when the split depends
      on a non-first column of the index (Paul Ramsey)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
为GiST索引页分裂修复不正确的逻辑，当分裂依赖于索引的非第一字段时 (Paul Ramsey)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Don't error out if recycling or removing an old WAL file fails at the
      end of checkpoint (Heikki)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
如果回收或删除一个老的WAL文件在检查点的结束失败，那么不要错误输出 (Heikki)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      It's better to treat the problem as non-fatal and allow the checkpoint
      to complete.  Future checkpoints will retry the removal.  Such problems
      are not expected in normal operation, but have been seen to be
      caused by misdesigned Windows anti-virus and backup software.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
最好将这个问题看做是不重要的，并且允许检查点完成。未来的检查点将重试移除。
这样的问题在正常的操作中不会出现，但是已经看到会由错误设计Windows杀毒和备份软件引起。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Ensure WAL files aren't repeatedly archived on Windows (Heikki)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
确保WAL文件不会在Windows上反复的归档 (Heikki)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This is another symptom that could happen if some other process
      interfered with deletion of a no-longer-needed file.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
如果一些其他进程介入不再需要的文件的删除中，这会是另外一个可能会发生的现象。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix PAM password processing to be more robust (Tom)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复PAM口令处理，使其更加强健 (Tom)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      The previous code is known to fail with the combination of the Linux
      <literal>pam_krb5</> PAM module with Microsoft Active Directory as the
      domain controller.  It might have problems elsewhere too, since it was
      making unjustified assumptions about what arguments the PAM stack would
      pass to it.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
都知道以前的代码在组合Linux <literal>pam_krb5</> PAM模块和微软活动目录作为域控制器时会失败。
可能在其他地方也会有问题，因为它关于PAM堆栈会传送来什么参数做了不正确的假设。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix processing of ownership dependencies during <literal>CREATE OR
      REPLACE FUNCTION</> (Tom)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复<literal>CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION</>期间所有权依赖关系的处理 (Tom)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix bug with calling <literal>plperl</> from <literal>plperlu</> or vice
      versa (Tom)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复从<literal>plperlu</>调用<literal>plperl</>或反过来调用时的bug (Tom)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      An error exit from the inner function could result in crashes due to
      failure to re-select the correct Perl interpreter for the outer function.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
从内部函数出错退出会导致由于未能为外部函数重新选择正确的Perl解释器而崩溃。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix session-lifespan memory leak when a PL/Perl function is redefined
      (Tom)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复PL/Perl函数重新定义了时会话寿命内存泄露 (Tom)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Ensure that Perl arrays are properly converted to
      <productname>PostgreSQL</> arrays when returned by a set-returning
      PL/Perl function (Andrew Dunstan, Abhijit Menon-Sen)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
确保当通过设置返回PL/Perl函数返回时，Perl数组正确的转换到了
<productname>PostgreSQL</>数组 (Andrew Dunstan, Abhijit Menon-Sen)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This worked correctly already for non-set-returning functions.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
非设置返回函数早已正确的工作了。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix rare crash in exception processing in PL/Python (Peter)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
